Tcl (1990) doesn&#x27;t directly have macros, but with a calling convention that resembles fexprs it doesn&#x27;t need them:<p><pre><code>    proc swap {_a _b} {
        upvar 1 $_a a
        upvar 1 $_b b
        foreach a $b b $a {}
    }
</code></pre>
Foreach is a builtin, but is trivially defined as:<p><pre><code>    proc each {ls script} {
        for {set i 0} {$i<[llength $ls]} {incr i} {
            uplevel 1 $script
        }
    }
</code></pre>
Perhaps more interesting:<p><pre><code>    proc until {cond script} {
        tailcall while &quot;!($cond)&quot; $script
    }</code></pre>
